The paper deals with object recognition in images, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm is a feature learning algorithm that uses autoencoders, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also involves learning features that are robust to variations across domains, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a classifier, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the algorithm on benchmark image recognition datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
